## Attributes System

### On Headings

# Main Title {#top}

## Section {.important}

### Subsection {#intro .section data-level=3}

### On Inline Elements

This is [special text]{.highlight}.

A [span with ID]{#unique-span}.

[Multiple attributes]{#id .class1 .class2}.

### Comments in Attributes

Attributes can contain comments that won't be visible:

This is [text]{#id % comment here % .class} with attributes.

## Smart Punctuation

Ellipsis: waiting...

Em dash: Used for breaks---like this.

En dash: Pages 10--20.

## Inline Formatting Showcase

### Superscript and Subscript

Chemical formula: H~2~O

Mathematical notation: x^2^ + y^2^

Combined: E = mc^2^ (mass in kg~0~)

### Highlight, Insert, Delete

{=Highlighted text=} stands out.

{+Inserted content+} shows additions.

{-Deleted content-} shows removals.

Track changes: {-old text-} {+new text+}

## Forced Delimiters

When you need explicit control:

{_Forced emphasis opener for edge cases

Forced closer_} here

Similarly for strong: {*forced strong opener

And closer*} works

## Reference Definitions with Attributes

{#main-link .external}
[example]: https://example.com

Links using [example][] inherit the attributes.

## Complex Combinations

A paragraph with _emphasis_, *strong*, `code`, [link](url), and ![image](img.jpg){.thumb}.

Math: $`x^2`, footnote[^1], and :emoji: symbols work together.

Formatted span: [This has _emphasis_ and *strong*]{.special #formatted}.
